adjectives.description: impacted (comparative more impacted, superlative most impacted)

entries.meaning: (dentistry) Of a tooth, subject to dental impaction.
examples: Being the last teeth to erupt in the oral cavity, many wisdom teeth are impacted.

entries.meaning: (US, economics) Having lost property revenue due to Federal presence, such that it may receive impact aid.
